# AGENT.md — FHEVM Development Guide for AI Coding Agents

> Generated by `fhevm-forge` and embedded in every scaffolded project.
> **Read this entire file before writing any code.** It encodes the API surface,
> working patterns, and silent-failure traps specific to this project.

---

## Quick Start — From Scaffold to Working dApp

```
1. Write / modify your contract in src/
2. Run forge test             — all tests must pass before deploying
3. fhevm-forge deploy --chains sepolia --contract <Name>
4. Paste the deployed address into frontend/app/contract.ts
5. cd frontend && npm run dev  — connect wallet on Sepolia and test
```

That is the complete loop. Every section below supports one of those five steps.

---

## Mental Model — How FHEVM Works

**Handles, not ciphertexts.**
When you store a `euint64`, the contract holds a 32-byte *handle* — a pointer into
the coprocessor's encrypted state. The actual ciphertext never lives on the host chain.
This is why you can pass handles around freely (they are opaque `bytes32` values),
but you cannot do arithmetic on them directly — all operations go through `FHE.*`
which dispatches to the coprocessor.

**Two chains, one abstraction.**

| Chain | Role | You interact with it? |
|-------|------|-----------------------|
| Host (Sepolia, chainId 11155111) | Contracts, wallets, handles | Yes — all your Solidity + TS code |
| Gateway (chainId 55815) | KMS, decryption oracle | Never directly |

The `@fhevm/sdk` workspace wraps `@zama-fhe/relayer-sdk` and hides the Gateway entirely.

**Public decrypt vs user decrypt — which to use?**

| | Public decrypt | User decrypt (reencrypt) |
|---|---|---|
| Who can trigger | Anyone (agent, script, keeper) | Only the owner of the value |
| Requires wallet | No | Yes — EIP-712 signature |
| Result goes to | On-chain callback | Browser / script memory |
| When to use | Health checks, auctions, liquidations | Showing a user their own balance |
| Solidity side | `Gateway.requestDecryption(handle, callback)` | No Solidity needed |
| TS side | `publicDecrypt([handle])` | `reencryptBatch(...)` / `useReencrypt` |

---

## File Map

```
src/              Solidity contracts (FHE encrypted state + operations)
test/             Forge tests — FhevmTest provides encrypt/decrypt helpers
script/           Forge deployment scripts

sdk/
  instance.ts     Singleton FhevmInstance (env-aware: browser / node / test)
  encrypt.ts      encryptValue, encryptUint64, encryptBatch — all encryption flows
  decrypt.ts      publicDecrypt, reencryptBatch — both decryption paths
  gateway.ts      pollForEvent, resolveHealthCheck, resolveAuctionBid helpers
  config.ts       Chain address registry (Sepolia, mainnet, Base, Arbitrum)
  errors.ts       FhevmError with actionable messages
  index.ts        Re-exports everything — use this in agent/script code

sdk/hooks/        Ethers-signer variants (no Wagmi, for agents + scripts)
frontend/hooks/   Wagmi-optimized hooks for Next.js components
  useEncrypt.ts        encrypt() → { handles, inputProof }
  useReencrypt.ts      reveal([handle]) → values[]

agent/
  fhevm-agent.ts  FhevmAgent class — headless, private-key-based runtime

frontend/
  app/providers.tsx    WagmiProvider + FhevmProvider wiring
  app/contract.ts      ABI + CONTRACT_ADDRESS — update after every deploy
  app/page.tsx         Main UI — reference implementation for Counter
```

