## Deployment

```bash
cp .env.example .env          # fill in SEPOLIA_RPC_URL + DEPLOYER_PRIVATE_KEY
fhevm-forge deploy --chains sepolia --contract Counter
fhevm-forge deploy --chains sepolia --contract Counter --dry-run   # simulate first
fhevm-forge deploy --chains sepolia,base --contract Counter        # multi-chain
```

After deploying, update `frontend/app/contract.ts` with the new address and ABI.

---

## Gas Reference

| Operation | On-Chain Gas | Coprocessor Gas |
|-----------|-------------|-----------------|
| `FHE.add` / `FHE.sub` | 8,000 | 65,000 |
| `FHE.mul` | 15,000 | 150,000 |
| `FHE.div` | 30,000 | 400,000 |
| `FHE.lt` / `le` / `gt` / `ge` / `eq` | 10,000 | 70,000 |
| `FHE.select` | 12,000 | 90,000 |
| `FHE.asEuint64` (public constant) | 6,000 | 50,000 |
| `FHE.fromExternal` (user input) | 6,000 | 50,000 |
| `FHE.allow` / `FHE.allowThis` | 3,000 | 0 |
| `FHE.allowTransient` | ~1,000 | 0 |
| `Gateway.requestDecryption` | 25,000 | 200,000 |

`fhevm-forge gas` prints a per-operation breakdown for your contracts.

---

## Anti-Patterns and Common Mistakes

### Solidity

| Code | Problem | Fix |
|------|---------|-----|
| `function f() public view returns (ebool)` | FHE ops write coprocessor state — `view` reverts | Remove `view` |
| `_balance = FHE.add(...)` with no `allowThis` | Handle permanently unreadable next call | `FHE.allowThis(_balance)` after every assignment |
| `FHE.allow(h, addr)` for same-tx cross-contract | Wastes ACL storage; semantically wrong | Use `FHE.allowTransient(h, addr)` |
| `external onlyGateway` missing on callback | Anyone can call with arbitrary cleartext | Add `onlyGateway` to every `fulfill*` function |
| `if (FHE.decrypt(condition))` inside a tx | Requires Gateway round-trip — will revert | Use `FHE.select(condition, a, b)` |
| Old imports (`TFHE`, `SepoliaZamaFHEVMConfig`) | Compile error / wrong addresses | Use `FHE`, `ZamaEthereumConfig` |

### TypeScript / Frontend

| Code | Problem | Fix |
|------|---------|-----|
| `args: [encrypted.handles[0], encrypted.inputProof]` | `Uint8Array` serialized incorrectly by Wagmi | Hex-encode: `` `0x${Buffer.from(...).toString("hex")}` `` |
| Reusing `inputProof` for a different contract | Proof is contract-bound — will revert | Generate a fresh proof per contract |
| `const fhe = await createInstance(...)` per call | Recreates WASM instance — slow | Use `getFhevmInstance("sepolia")` singleton |
| `const { abiEncodedClearValues } = await publicDecrypt(...)` | Field does not exist | Destructure `{ results, clearValues }` |
| `const h = handles[2]` from a 2-value getter | Silent `undefined` | Use named destructuring from Solidity named returns |
| Rendering FHE UI before `useFhevm().ready` | Crashes on WASM not loaded | Gate on `fheLoading` / `fheError` first |

### Testing

| Mistake | Fix |
|---------|-----|
| `contract MyTest is Test` | Use `FhevmTest` — it provides `encryptUint64`, `decrypt`, etc. |
| Forgetting `super.setUp()` in `setUp()` | FhevmTest coprocessor mock not initialized — all FHE ops revert |
| `assertEq(counter.getHandle(), expectedHandle)` | Handles are opaque — decrypt first: `assertEq(decrypt(euint64.wrap(handle)), 42)` |
| Calling `encrypt(...)` without `vm.prank` | Proof is bound to `msg.sender` — mismatched user fails verification |

---

## Error Code Index

| Code | Message / Symptom | Root Cause | Fix |
|------|-------------------|------------|-----|
| FHEVM-001 | State silently corrupted after write | Missing `FHE.allowThis()` | Call after every `euint` assignment |
| FHEVM-002 | External contract reverts reading handle | Missing `FHE.allow(h, contract)` | Add before cross-contract call |
| FHEVM-003 | Function reverts with FHE op inside | `view` modifier on FHE function | Remove `view` |
| FHEVM-004 | Same-tx cross-contract handle unreadable | Used `allow` instead of `allowTransient` | Use `FHE.allowTransient` |
| FHEVM-005 | Contract reverts on `fromExternal` | Proof reused across contracts | New proof per contract |
| FHEVM-006 | Gateway callback callable by anyone | Missing `onlyGateway` | Add to all `fulfill*` callbacks |
| FHEVM-007 | `clearValues` undefined | Wrong `publicDecrypt` destructuring | Use `{ results, clearValues }` |
| FHEVM-008 | `handles[N]` is `undefined` | Indexed past getter return count | Use named Solidity returns + named destructuring |
| FHEVM-009 | `TFHE` / `SepoliaZamaFHEVMConfig` not found | Old API imports | Use `FHE` / `ZamaEthereumConfig` |
| FHEVM-010 | Wagmi rejects ciphertext argument | `Uint8Array` passed directly | `` `0x${Buffer.from(h).toString("hex")}` `` |
| FHEVM-011 | FhevmTest ops revert in tests | `super.setUp()` not called | First line of `setUp()` override |
| FHEVM-012 | `if (FHE.decrypt(...))` reverts | Decrypt requires async Gateway | Use `FHE.select(condition, a, b)` |
| FHEVM-013 | `SenderNotAllowedToUseHandle` on `fromExternal` | `InputVerifierAddress` or `relayerUrl` or `gatewayChainId` is wrong — proof was generated against the wrong contract | Set the three Sepolia values from the **Sepolia Configuration** section above |

---

## Environment Variables

```bash
# .env (Foundry / agent)
SEPOLIA_RPC_URL=           # Alchemy/Infura Sepolia endpoint
DEPLOYER_PRIVATE_KEY=      # Wallet deploying contracts
AGENT_PRIVATE_KEY=         # Separate key for headless agent
ETHERSCAN_API_KEY=         # etherscan.io — for contract verification
MAINNET_RPC_URL=
BASE_RPC_URL=
ARBITRUM_RPC_URL=

# frontend/.env.local
NEXT_PUBLIC_SEPOLIA_RPC_URL=   # Public RPC — exposed to browser
```

